{"article_id":"oZXgSnTvkezMa8yX","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Senators are scheduled to be on a break from Washington for the next two weeks ,","depth":6},{"id":1,"text":"but they have left behind a rearguard","depth":8},{"id":2,"text":"to keep the chamber running on low gear ,","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"denying President Obama a chance","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"to install his Supreme Court nominee .","depth":8},{"id":5,"text":"It ' s part of Republicans ' vow","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"to do everything","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"to keep Mr. Obama from replacing the late Justice Antonin Scalia ,","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"whose death last month left the court divided 4-4 ,","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"and left Democrats salivating over the opportunity","depth":10},{"id":10,"text":"to replace the conservative Scalia with a liberal .","depth":10},{"id":11,"text":"Mr. Obama last week nominated Judge Merrick Garland , an appeals court judge in the District of Columbia ,","depth":6},{"id":12,"text":"to fill Scalia ' s seat .","depth":6},{"id":13,"text":"Judge Garland has received near universal praise for his qualifications and temperament .","depth":6},{"id":14,"text":"Still some advocacy groups important to Republicans , such as the National Rifle Association and the National Federation of Independent Business , have given him low marks for rulings .","depth":6},{"id":15,"text":"Republican leaders didn ' t budge in their vow","depth":6},{"id":16,"text":"to deny any Obama nominee a hearing , much less a vote ,","depth":6},{"id":17,"text":"saying","depth":6},{"id":18,"text":"the responsibility","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"for picking a replacement","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"should rest with the next president .","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"SEE ALSO :","depth":5},{"id":22,"text":"Merrick Garland denied review to pro-life priests","depth":6},{"id":23,"text":"challenging contraceptive mandate","depth":6},{"id":24,"text":"Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell , Kentucky Republican , flatly ruled out any action again Sunday ,","depth":5},{"id":25,"text":"saying","depth":6},{"id":26,"text":"Judge Garland won ' t get a floor vote .","depth":6},{"id":27,"text":"\" The schedule in the Senate is set by the majority leader .","depth":5},{"id":28,"text":"And most of my members are very comfortable with letting the American people make this decision","depth":7},{"id":29,"text":"by electing the next president ,","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"who will fill this vacancy next year , \"","depth":8},{"id":31,"text":"Mr. McConnell told ABC ' s \" This Week \" program .","depth":6},{"id":32,"text":"Part of that strategy is denying Mr. Obama the opening","depth":7},{"id":33,"text":"to make a recess appointment .","depth":7},{"id":34,"text":"Senators have scheduled pro forma sessions","depth":8},{"id":35,"text":"to meet a couple of times a week ,","depth":9},{"id":36,"text":"with no business scheduled ,","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"specifically to deny Mr. Obama that chance .","depth":7},{"id":38,"text":"Under Senate rules , that is enough","depth":7},{"id":39,"text":"to prevent the constitutional trigger","depth":8},{"id":40,"text":"that would let Mr. Obama deem the Senate in recess","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"and make an appointment","depth":10},{"id":42,"text":"without them .","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"\" It ' s very smart for the Senate to take every conceivable precaution","depth":8},{"id":44,"text":"to ensure","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"the president doesn ' t try to recess appoint his nominee , \"","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"said Brian Rogers at America Rising Squared , a conservative pressure group .","depth":7},{"id":47,"text":"When the Scalia seat opened last month ,","depth":8},{"id":48,"text":"the Senate had just entered a full recess for Presidents Day ,","depth":8},{"id":49,"text":"and some scholars argued","depth":8},{"id":50,"text":"that Mr. Obama could have pulled the trigger on an appointment then .","depth":8},{"id":51,"text":"Thanks to Republican tactics , that avenue is likely closed for good .","depth":6},{"id":52,"text":"Senate Minority Leader Harry Reid , Nevada Democrat , predicted","depth":8},{"id":53,"text":"that Mr. McConnell will eventually cave","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"when pressure grows too high on his fellow Republicans .","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"\" I don ' t know","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"why McConnell ' s done this to his senators , \"","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"Mr. Reid told NBC ' s \" Meet the Press \" on Sunday .","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"\" He ' s marching them over a cliff ,","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"and I don ' t think","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"they ' re going to go . \"","depth":10},{"id":61,"text":"He and other Democrats said","depth":8},{"id":62,"text":"they saw the first signs of cracks in the blockade last week","depth":9},{"id":63,"text":"when several Republican senators said","depth":10},{"id":64,"text":"they would consider confirming Judge Garland in a lame-duck session late this year","depth":11},{"id":65,"text":"if Hillary Clinton wins the presidential election .","depth":11},{"id":66,"text":"But Mr. McConnell ruled out even that possibility ,","depth":8},{"id":67,"text":"saying","depth":9},{"id":68,"text":"the next president ,","depth":11},{"id":69,"text":"no matter who wins the election ,","depth":11},{"id":70,"text":"will fill the seat .","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"With Washington going on Easter break ,","depth":4},{"id":72,"text":"both sides are increasing their efforts","depth":5},{"id":73,"text":"to defend their stances to voters back home .","depth":5},{"id":74,"text":"The Judicial Crisis Network , a conservative group , has vowed to spend $ 2 million","depth":6},{"id":75,"text":"to defend a couple of Republican senators","depth":8},{"id":76,"text":"who are balking at Mr. Obama ' s pick","depth":8},{"id":77,"text":"and to go after several Democrats ,","depth":8},{"id":78,"text":"demanding","depth":9},{"id":79,"text":"that they oppose the president ' s effort","depth":10},{"id":80,"text":"to shift the court to the left .","depth":10},{"id":81,"text":"Liberal groups , meanwhile , are rallying editorial pages back home ,","depth":6},{"id":82,"text":"arguing","depth":7},{"id":83,"text":"that","depth":8},{"id":84,"text":"by refusing to vote on Judge Garland ,","depth":9},{"id":85,"text":"Republicans in the Senate are flouting their constitutional responsibilities .","depth":9},{"id":86,"text":"Polling suggests","depth":6},{"id":87,"text":"that Democrats are winning the debate ,","depth":6},{"id":88,"text":"with even Republican voters saying","depth":6},{"id":89,"text":"the Senate should hold hearings on Judge Garland .","depth":6},{"id":90,"text":"The Congressional Research Service said","depth":6},{"id":91,"text":"the Scalia vacancy is unique in modern American political history .","depth":6},{"id":92,"text":"\" It is the only vacancy","depth":8},{"id":93,"text":"that has existed during the eighth , and final , year of a presidency","depth":8},{"id":94,"text":"that also arose during the eighth year itself , \"","depth":7},{"id":95,"text":"the organization said in a legal memo last week .","depth":6},{"id":96,"text":"Several seats have come open in the final year of a president ' s term ,","depth":6},{"id":97,"text":"but in each of those instances it was","depth":7},{"id":98,"text":"when a president was running for re-election .","depth":7},{"id":99,"text":"The Congressional Research Service said","depth":6},{"id":100,"text":"there has been one recess appointment of a Supreme Court justice during a presidential election year ,","depth":7},{"id":101,"text":"when President Eisenhower installed William J. Brennan in 1956 .","depth":8},{"id":102,"text":"Brennan was confirmed to a complete term in 1957 .","depth":8},{"id":103,"text":"Ironically , it was Mr. Obama ' s own aggressive tactics","depth":5},{"id":104,"text":"that left him vulnerable to Republicans ' pro forma strategy","depth":6},{"id":105,"text":"to deny him recess appointment powers .","depth":6},{"id":106,"text":"In 2012 , Mr. Obama issued a slate of recess appointments","depth":7},{"id":107,"text":"even while the Senate was meeting every few days in pro forma sessions .","depth":7},{"id":108,"text":"He said","depth":8},{"id":109,"text":"pro forma sessions weren ' t really meetings ,","depth":8},{"id":110,"text":"so he was justified in his move .","depth":7},{"id":111,"text":"But the Supreme Court , in a unanimous 2014 ruling , held","depth":7},{"id":112,"text":"that Mr. Obama violated the Constitution","depth":8},{"id":113,"text":"in making those appointments .","depth":8},{"id":114,"text":"The justices said","depth":7},{"id":115,"text":"a recess had to be at least three days ,","depth":8},{"id":116,"text":"and in all but emergencies needed to be 10 days .","depth":8}],"relations":[{"parent":233,"left":187,"right":232,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":187,"left":140,"right":186,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":140,"left":131,"right":139,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":131,"left":127,"right":130,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":127,"left":121,"right":126,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":121,"left":0,"right":120,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":120,"left":118,"right":119,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":118,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":119,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":126,"left":5,"right":125,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":125,"left":6,"right":124,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":124,"left":7,"right":123,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":123,"left":8,"right":122,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":122,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":130,"left":128,"right":129,"r